## üöÄ NAVIGATION & FLOW CONTROL

### Admin Controls
- **Navigation Bar**:
  - Previous/Next buttons
  - Jump to specific submodule (dropdown)
  - Module overview (thumbnail grid)
  - Search modules
- **Keyboard Shortcuts**:
  - Arrow Left/Right: Previous/Next submodule
  - Number keys (1-9): Jump to submodule
  - Space: Pause/Resume auto-advance
  - F: Toggle fullscreen
  - P: Toggle presenter notes
  - Esc: Exit current module
- **Presentation Modes**:
  - Manual (admin controls all navigation)
  - Auto-advance (timed, configurable per submodule)
  - Self-paced (participants control their own view)
  - Hybrid (admin leads, participants can review previous slides)

### Client Experience
- **Synchronized View** (default):
  - Automatically follows admin's current submodule
  - Smooth transitions with animations
  - Loading indicators for heavy content
- **Free Navigation Mode** (optional):
  - Participants can browse at their own pace
  - Visual indicator shows where admin currently is
  - "Return to Live" button to sync back
- **Minimized Cards**:
  - Previous/next submodules shown as small previews
  - Expand on click or when admin navigates to them
  - Smooth accordion-style transitions
- **Progress Indicator**:
  - Dots/bars showing position in module
  - Estimated time remaining
  - Completed/current/upcoming visual states

---

## üíæ CONTENT STORAGE & OFFLINE ACCESS

### Storage Strategy

#### Lightweight Content (Database)
- Module structure and metadata
- Text content
- Configuration settings
- User progress and notes
- Quiz responses and poll results
- Small images (<500KB)

#### Heavy Content (External Storage)
- **Git LFS** (Large File Storage):
  - Videos
  - High-res images
  - PDF documents
  - Audio files
  - Large datasets
- **Benefits**:
  - Version control for media
  - Efficient storage
  - Easy collaboration
  - Free hosting on GitHub/GitLab
- **Structure**:
  ```
  /media
    /modules
      /module-id-1
        /images
        /videos
        /documents
      /module-id-2
  ```

#### Client-Side Caching
- **Service Worker**:
  - Cache viewed content automatically
  - Offline-first strategy
  - Background sync when online
- **IndexedDB**:
  - Store user notes and bookmarks
  - Cache module structure
  - Save quiz progress
- **localStorage**:
  - User preferences
  - Theme settings
  - Last viewed position

### Offline Package Export
- **"Download for Offline"** button:
  - Creates a standalone HTML package
  - Includes all media for selected modules
  - Fully functional without server
  - Includes glossary, notes, resources
  - Compressed ZIP file
- **Selective Download**:
  - Choose which modules to include
  - Option to exclude heavy media
  - Estimated package size shown
- **Update Mechanism**:
  - Check for updates when online
  - Download only changed content
  - Version comparison

